This paper is primarily focused on data management systems and their ability to support both long-running analytics queries and short-lived transactions. This topic falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of distributed systems and main-memory storage, which are relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and operating systems (cs.OS). The use of B-trees is a common data structure in computer science, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the system, which is relevant to computer performance evaluation and benchmarking (cs.DC).
